{"cursor":"24425","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{Infobox U.S. legislation\n| shorttitle= Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act longtitle= To prohibit the\n| movement in interstate commerce of adulterated and misbranded food, drugs,\n| devices, and cosmetics, and for other purposes. acronym= FFDCA, \"FD&C Act\"\n| enacted by= 75th effective date= public law url=\n| http://research.archives.gov/description/299847 cite public law= 75-717 cite\n| statutes at large= acts repealed= Pure Food and Drug Act acts amended= title\n| amended= sections created= Chapter 9 Â§ 301 et seq. sections amended=\n| leghisturl= introducedin= Senate introducedbill= introducedby= Royal Copeland\n| (DâNY) introduceddate= March 5, 1938 committees= Committee on Interstate and\n| Foreign Commerce passedbody1= House passeddate1= June 1, 1938 passedvote1=\n| amended and passed passedbody2= Senate passeddate2= June 2, 1938 passedvote2=\n| disagreed conferencedate= June 11, 1938 passedbody3= House passeddate3= June\n| 15, 1938 passedvote3= agreed passedbody4= Senate passeddate4= June 15, 1938\n| passedvote4= agreed signedpresident= Franklin D. Roosevelt signeddate= June\n| 25, 1938 amendments=\n*1951 Food, Drug, and Cosmetics Act Amendments, PL 82â215, 65 Stat 648 *1962\nFood, Drug, and Cosmetics Act Amendments, PL 87â781, 76 Stat 780 *Fair Packaging\nand Labeling Act, PL 89â755, 80 Stat 1296 *Medical Device Regulation Act, PL\n94â295, 90 Stat 539 *Radiation Control for Safety and Health Act, PL 90-602, 82\nStat 1173 *Drug Price Competition and Patent Term Restoration Act of 1984, PL\n98-471, 98 Stat 1585 *Nutrition Labeling and Education Act (1990), PL 101-535,\n104 Stat 2353 *Safe Medical Device Amendments of 1990, PL 101-629, 104 Stat 4511\n*Food and Drug Administration Revitalization Act (1990), PL 101-635, 104 Stat\n4583 *Dietary Supplement Health and Education Act (1994), PL 103-417, 108 Stat\n4332 *Food and Drug Administration Modernization Act of 1997, PL 105-115, 111\nStat 2296 *Food and Drug Administration Amendments Act of 2007, PL 110-85, 121\nStat 823 \"[http://www.ll.georgetown.edu/guides/fooddruglaw.cfm Food, Drug,\nand Cosmetic Law Research Guide],\" Georgetown Law Library }}\n\nThe United States 'Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act' (abbreviated as\n'FFDCA', 'FDCA', or 'FD&C'), is a set of laws passed by Congress in 1938 giving\nauthority to the U.S. Food and Drug Administration (FDA) to oversee the safety\nof food, drugs, and cosmetics. A principal author of this law was Royal S.\nCopeland, a three-term U.S. Senator from New\nYork. [http://www.homeowatch.org/history/reghx.html Homeopathic Drugs, Royal\nCopeland, and Federal Drug Regulation ] In\n1968, the Electronic Product Radiation Control provisions were added to the\nFD&C. Also in that year the FDA formed the Drug Efficacy Study Implementation\n(DESI) to incorporate into FD&C regulations the recommendations from a National\nAcademy of Sciences investigation of effectiveness of previously marketed\ndrugs. [http://www.fda.gov/cder/about/history/time1.htm CDER - Time Line ] The act has been amended many times, most\nrecently to add requirements about bioterrorism preparations.\n\nThe introduction of this act was influenced by the death of more than 100\npatients due to a sulfanilamide medication where diethylene glycol was used to\ndissolve the drug and make a liquid\nform. [http://www.ashp.org/s_ashp/article_news.asp?CID=167&DID=2024&id=3659\nASHP Website : News Article ] See Elixir\nSulfanilamide disaster. It replaced the earlier Pure Food and Drug Act of 1906.\n","linknr":389,"url":"Food,_Drug_and_Cosmetic_Act","recorded":1376421849,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Federal_Food,_Drug,_and_Cosmetic_Act&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Federal_Food,_Drug,_and_Cosmetic_Act&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Speci